<h2 class="accordion-header">What is an e-commerce website?</h2>
<div class="accordion-content">
<p>E-Commerce websites are online retail platforms that function as digitized "portals" to help e-commerce. Any website with an e-commerce system through which customers can buy a product or service is an E-Commerce Website. Sites may be simple template-driven plug-and-play solutions, or they might be incredibly sophisticated portals requiring thousands of lines of code to operate.</p>
</div>
<h2 class="accordion-header">Why is your e-commerce website important?</h2>
<div class="accordion-content">
<p>The Internet has allowed businesses to reach an enormous audience with less investment than traditional brick and mortar stores. It has also created new problems for businesses with regard to competition, customer acquisition, and online marketing. With more than half of all internet traffic now originating from smartphones, your online storefront must function well on various platforms.</p>
</div>
<h2 class="accordion-header">Is it possible to create eCommerce websites that are database-driven?</h2>
<div class="accordion-content">
<p>A database-driven or dynamic website, in which content generated outside of the site files is stored in a database. This allows you to collect, present, and manage your data quickly and easily.</p>
<p>E-commerce websites that rely on database technology are the most popular e-commerce website. The major benefit of employing these systems is that data or information can be readily updated using a simple user interface. Product management is the most difficult aspect for an e-commerce platform, and it may be effectively handled by a database-driven e-commerce website</p>
<p>Web Choice can help you develop database-driven and secure e-commerce websites. We can also assist with any existing e-commerce website; we can assist with modifications and updates to help you manage online databases and get better results.</p>
</div>
<h2 class="accordion-header">What platforms available for eCommerce website development?</h2>
<div class="accordion-content">
<p>Choosing the e-commerce platform for your site before you begin is critical. Your choice will have a significant influence on your consumers' e-commerce experience.</p>
<p>There are several e-commerce website CMSs on the market, and they're all excellent. Here are some e-commerce website suggestions that provide you with simplicity without sacrificing quality or functionality.</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Opencart</b> - Opencart is the most popular alternative. It's a lightning-fast platform with simple tools to help you get started. Opencart is an e-commerce platform that provides everything you'll need to start an online business, as well as tools for managing your inventory and processing sales.</li>
<li><b>Magento</b> - Magento is ideal for those who have a website with a lot of products and are more technically competent. Magento is one of the most popular open-source e-commerce solutions. It offers a wide selection of themes, as well as some impressive capabilities. This platform allows you to completely customize any number of products in your store.</li>
<li><b>BigCommerce</b>- eCommerce software from BigCommerce is a fantastic solution for rapidly scaling up an online business. This CMS has extensive sales tools built-in and integrates them with sophisticated SEO and multi-channel connectivity.</li>
<li><b>Woocommerce</b> - this is a very popular e-commerce platform, which is presently implemented on more than three million websites.
<br><br>
The above list is just a sample of what's available; there are many other e-commerce platforms that Web Choice can assist you with.
</li>
</ul>
</div>
